thics, the family, human nature, and religiousness—thus engaging Dewey with themes generally associated with Confucian thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEast and West. 0aPhilosophy, Chinese. 0aPhilosophy, Comparative. 0aPhilosophy, Confucian. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : American Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Comparative Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Eastern / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847448940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438474489423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438474489/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles